As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 961 people, 175 households, and 147 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2020: Golden Beach town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Golden+Beach+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 919 people, 236 households, and 202 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2010: Golden Beach town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Golden+Beach+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

===2000 census===
In 2000, 49.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 72.3% were married couples living together, 8.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 17.0% were non-families. 13.8% of all households were made up of individuals, and 8.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.26 and the average family size was 3.55.

In 2000, the town population was spread out, with 34.6% under the age of 18, 3.5% from 18 to 24, 24.5% from 25 to 44, 26.2% from 45 to 64, and 11.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.4 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 85.5 males.

In 2000, the median income for a household in the town was $136,686, and the median income for a family was $141,557. Males had a median income of $81,193 versus $58,750 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $73,053.

As of 2000, speakers of [[English language|English]] as a [[first language]] accounted for 55.01% of the population, while [[Spanish language|Spanish]] accounted for 35.09% of the populace, speakers of [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] made up 4.40%, [[French language|French]] was at 3.85%, and [[Russian language|Russian]] was the [[mother tongue]] for 1.65% of residents.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=&zip=&place_id=26250&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA's Data Center Results of Golden Beach, FL |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |access-date=October 27, 2007}}</ref>

